        void intersectWith(java.util.Set<E> a)
        Retains only elements within this set which are contained in the parameter set. The method "equals()" is used to detect identity. This is a destructive method.

        a - Set<E> argument set

      • uniteWith

        void uniteWith(java.util.Set<E> a)
        Adds all elements from the parameter set which are not already contained in this set into this set. The method "equals()" is used to detect identity. This is a creative method.
        Parameters:
        a - Set<E> argument set

      • exclude

        void exclude(java.util.Set<E> a)

      • xorWith

        void xorWith(java.util.Set<E> a)
        Retains elements of this set which are not contained in the parameter set, while it unites with all elements from the parameter set which are not contained in this set. The method "equals()" is used to detect identity. This is both creative and destructive.
        Parameters:
        a - Set<E> argument set
